commentary: Arafat Sunny to Sami Aslam, no run Aslam looks to paddle, lobs it through to leg slip. Smart catch from Tamim. Big appeal from Bangladesh, but it amounts to nothing. Tamim wants a review. The ball looped off the pad, Tamim followed the ball, tumbled back and pouched a brilliant catch. No glove involved. Pitched outside leg, so no chances of giving it out via lbw. Bangladesh's review ends in vain

commentary: Nasir Hossain to Sami Aslam, OUT Aslam has nicked off or has he?. The crowd find their voice again. Pushed through a bit outside off, spins away as well, leaving Aslam prodding. The keeper pouches it. And it is given, though there was no outside edge on that. Aslam did not review. Azhar should have insisted on the review. Actually, replays show that the ball grazed the bottom thumb on its way to Mushfiq

commentary: Mashrafe Mortaza to Azhar Ali, 2 runs good length ball outside off, he shuffles across, steps out, twirls his wrists and flicks it wide of midwicket for his maiden ODI century. commentary: Shakib Al Hasan to Azhar Ali, OUT Shakib strikes with the arm-ball. This was angled in with some good extra bounce. Azhar shifts his balance onto the back foot in an attempt to cut it away. It was far too close to play the stroke and Azhar failed to connect. Shakib hits the top of off. His joy may translate as you miss and I hit. Azhar slams his bat on the ground as he trudges back

commentary: Junaid Khan to Tamim Iqbal, OUT Tamim Iqbal has been given out lbw, he goes for a review straightaway. This was fuller and angled in, Tamim is hit on the knee-roll of the front pad in front of off. Hawk-Eye shows that it would hit top of off. The on-field umpire's decision is vindicated. No hat-trick of centuries for Tamim. Nevertheless, he gets a standing ovation as he walks back
